data.name: City Studio at The Commodore
data.description:
The iconic Commodore building is a historic property with a rich history dating back to the early 20th century.
Built in 1898, The Commodore is a Chicago landmark known for its elegant Beaux-Arts architecture, featuring a classic U-shaped courtyard design that fosters a sense of community and timeless charm.
Originally constructed as a luxury apartment hotel, The Commodore was later converted into condominiums and now houses over 100 unique units, blending historic character with modern updates.
Managed by the Commodore Greenbriar Landmark Condo Association, the building remains a cornerstone of the Lakeview East neighborhood, offering residents a well-maintained and secure living environment. Its prime location provides easy access to Lake Michigan, vibrant nightlife, & a variety of dining and shopping options.
City Studio by ARIBIA reflects its heritage, while offering contemporary amenities, creating a harmonious blend of history & modern living. 

www.CommodoreChicago.com

data.name: Cozy Castle at The Commodore
data.description:
Historic luxury meets modern convenience at The Commodore, 550 W Surf. Built in 1897 by architect Edmund R. Krause, this six‑story Roman‑brick landmark anchors Lakeview East’s Surf‑Pine Grove historic district. Beyond the gated courtyard await elevator service, bike storage, package room, new sprinklers, and on‑site management - also included is cable and gigabit internet. Inside, original woodwork, oversized windows, and a legendary 6th‑floor ballroom rumored to host Capone‑era soirées deliver Gilded‑Age drama. Trader Joe’s, Target, gyms, lakefront trail, and Wrigley Field are minutes away.

https://CommodoreChicago.com

data.name: Lakeside Loft at Addison Lakeshore West
data.description:
Addison Lakeshore West is a beautifully preserved vintage courtyard building in Chicago’s Lakeview neighborhood, constructed in the 1920s. This boutique-style property combines timeless architectural charm with modern-day convenience. Its standout feature is a landscaped courtyard, complete with manicured gardens, mature trees, & a tranquil fountain, offering a serene retreat from city life.

The building emphasizes secure living with an access control system, ensuring privacy & peace of mind for all residents. Pet-friendly, the property welcomes your furry companions, fostering a community-oriented environment. With only a limited number of units, residents enjoy an intimate, close-knit atmosphere that is ideal for those seeking a quieter urban lifestyle.

Situated just steps from Lake Michigan, public transportation & renowned dining & shopping, Lakeside Loft is a harmonious blend of history, style, & convenience, making it a true gem in the heart of Lakeview  LakesideLoftChicago.com

data.description:
8-Min Walk to Illinois Masonic | Fully Renovated 2023 | Smart Home | Pet Haven | All-Inclusive

Thoughtfully curated 360 sqft sanctuary in Chicago's coveted Lakeview East, where even your four-legged companions are welcomed with the same sophisticated hospitality extended to their bipedal counterparts. Custom quartz countertops, IKEA cabinetry with soft-close drawers, professional blackout curtains, pullout for guests. Ring, Nest, & Alexa integration.

Available dedicated garage parking spot because even in walkable Lakeview East, sometimes one requires the automotive dignity of arrival.

Perfect for traveling medical professionals seeking proximity to healing institutions . 

| Avail November 1 | $2,450-2,650/mo  | Hskp & Pkng avail upon request for additional consideration | (utility cap of $75/mo)
